            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_ponding_initial_state",
                    "description": "All variables at their declared defaults (h = 0.01 m, omega = 1.0e-4 m, P = 2.0e-6 m/s, I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s) sampled at t = 0. Pins the head and the two algebraic variables at the start of the canonical ponding scenario: with h/omega = 100 the surface is well into the ponded regime, so the smoothed Heaviside eta_omega = (1/pi)*atan(100) + 1/2 is close to 1, and the smoothed Dirac delta_omega = (1/pi)*omega/(omega^2 + h^2) is far down its tail. Tolerance tightened to rel = 1e-9 because at t = 0 there is no integration drift -- only the parser->Float64 conversion and the first algebraic evaluation.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "tolerance": {
                        "rel": 1e-09
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "h",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.01
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "η_ω",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9968170072350918
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "δ_ω",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.31827805837795287
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "default_ponding_100s",
                    "description": "Default scenario integrated for 100 s. Reproduces the upstream test 'Net positive flux increases head' (test/surface_runoff_test.jl:293-309) quantitatively: with the net flux P - I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s > 0 the surface ponds and the head rises. The expected h(100) is the exact root of the conserved quantity eta_omega(h)*h = eta_omega(0.01)*0.01 + (P - I_infil)*100 -- the head increases from 1.00 cm to ~1.01 cm. The endpoint eta_omega confirms the surface stays in the ponded regime throughout. The t = 0 assertion keeps rel = 1e-9; the integrated endpoints use the model-level rel = 1e-6.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 100.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "h",
