                            "expected": 0.9968485199517559
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "heaviside_at_transition_zero_flux",
                    "description": "Head pinned at the ponding/unsaturated transition (h = 0) with zero net flux (P = I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s). Reproduces the upstream 'Smoothed Heaviside properties' check eta_omega(h = 0) = 0.5 (test/surface_runoff_test.jl:266) -- atan(0) = 0 so eta_omega = (1/pi)*0 + 1/2 = 0.5 exactly -- and simultaneously exercises the zero-net-flux equilibrium: P - I_infil = 0 makes D(h) exactly 0.0, so h, eta_omega and delta_omega stay fixed for all time. The same values are asserted at t = 0 and t = 50 to confirm the head does not drift. At h = 0 the smoothed Dirac delta is at its peak delta_omega = 1/(pi*omega).",
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "h": 0.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "P": 1e-06,
                        "I_infil": 1e-06
                    },
