                {
                    "id": "unsaturated_to_saturated_transition",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream test 'Transition from unsaturated to saturated' (test/surface_runoff_test.jl:311-331): the head starts negative (h0 = -0.05 m, unsaturated), precipitation P = 1.0e-5 m/s with no infiltration drives it positive over 10000 s, with omega = 1.0e-3 m. The conserved quantity gives the trajectory exactly: at t = 5000 s the head reaches +0.05 m (by the wetting symmetry Phi(h) - Phi(-h) = h, the midpoint of the +-0.05 m swing lands precisely at +0.05 m) and at t = 10000 s it reaches +0.10 m, with eta_omega ~ 1 confirming the surface has switched fully into the ponded regime. The early head excursion through the near-singular denominator (delta_omega*h + eta_omega -> small as h -> negative) is a fast transient; tolerance is relaxed to rel = 1e-5 for the integrated points, rel = 1e-9 at t = 0.",
