            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "ponding_head_rise",
                    "description": "Headline run: the canonical ponding scenario (defaults -- h0 = 0.01 m, P = 2.0e-6 m/s, I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s, omega = 1.0e-4 m) integrated for 100 s. With a positive net flux the surface ponds and the pressure head rises slowly and almost linearly (the smoothed Heaviside eta_omega is near 1 in the ponded regime, so d/dt[eta_omega*h] = P - I_infil reduces to dh/dt ~ P - I_infil). Plots the head h(t) and the smoothed Heaviside indicator eta_omega(t) over the run.",
