                    "id": "wetting_transition_over_time",
                    "description": "A wetting run that carries the surface across the full transition: starting unsaturated at h0 = -0.05 m, precipitation P = 1.0e-5 m/s (no infiltration) drives the head to +0.10 m over 10000 s, with omega = 1.0e-3 m. This reproduces the upstream test 'Transition from unsaturated to saturated' as a time series. The head h(t) climbs through zero near t = 5000 s; the smoothed Heaviside eta_omega(t) rises from ~0 (unsaturated) through 0.5 at the crossing to ~1 (ponded); and the smoothed Dirac delta_omega(t) spikes sharply to its peak 1/(pi*omega) exactly as the head crosses h = 0, then decays -- the continuous switch firing as the boundary condition flips.",
