                {
                    "id": "smoothing_parameter_sweep",
                    "description": "Sweep of the smoothing parameter omega across three orders of magnitude (1.0e-5 to 1.0e-2 m, logarithmic) at a fixed ponded head (h = 0.01 m) and zero net flux (P = I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s, so the head -- and hence eta_omega, delta_omega -- stays constant through each run). Surfaces how the smoothing parameter controls the approximation: as omega -> 0 the smoothed Heaviside eta_omega(h = 0.01) -> 1 (a sharp step) and the off-peak smoothed Dirac delta_omega -> 0; as omega grows the step softens and eta_omega relaxes toward 0.5.",
