                            "id": "dirac_vs_omega",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Smoothed Dirac delta delta_omega at the fixed head h = 0.01 m as a function of omega (log x axis). delta_omega = (1/pi)*omega/(omega^2 + h^2) rises with omega while omega << h, peaks where omega = h = 0.01 m, then falls.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "ω",
                                "label": "smoothing parameter omega (m)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "δ_ω",
                                "label": "smoothed Dirac delta delta_omega (m^-1)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "final_head_vs_precipitation",
                    "description": "Sweep of the precipitation flux P from 0 to 4.0e-6 m/s at fixed infiltration (I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s, the default) and the default ponded head (h0 = 0.01 m, omega = 1.0e-4 m), each run integrated 500 s. Surfaces the surface-runoff flux balance: the final head is governed by the net flux P - I_infil. For P < I_infil the surface drains and the head ends below its 1 cm start; at P = I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s the net flux is zero and the head is unchanged; for P > I_infil the surface ponds and the head ends above 1 cm. The final-head-versus-P curve is the equilibrium response of the boundary condition to the precipitation rate.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "I_infil": 1e-06
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 500.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "P",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.0,
                                    "stop": 4e-06,
                                    "count": 50,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "final_head_vs_P",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Final surface pressure head h after 500 s as a function of the precipitation flux P (infiltration fixed at I_infil = 1.0e-6 m/s). A monotonically increasing line crossing the unchanged-head level h = 0.01 m at P = I_infil: draining for P below that point, ponding above.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "P",
                                "label": "precipitation flux P (m/s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "h",
                                "label": "final pressure head h (m)"
